Results

As mentioned in t_particle is an auxiliary variable used in particle tracing simulations. It represents the time a particle has spent in the simulation domain since its release. Hence I exported the t_particle data for each velocity for each channel and then plotted their distributions ( FigureÂ 1, FigureÂ 6, FigureÂ 7, FigureÂ 8 ).

As plots all show skewed distributions, I think the geometric mean residence time and log-normal coefficient of variation are the appropriate statistics, but I calculated the arithmetic mean and sample standard deviation CV too just in case Iâm wrong (TableÂ 2, TableÂ 3, TableÂ 4, TableÂ 5).
